# Writing paradigm

- write on your thesis a little bit every day.
- diminishing returns in many tasks; try to do tasks a speed that gives you a sense of things moving forward, mistakes won't feel as mistakey if the effort involved was swift
- use sentences with ; for variation
- methods vs tools? Methods in non-technical parts, function in materials & methods
- object, class vs instance (of container)? Instance
- data structure vs data container?
- health outcomes
- multi-modal microbiome research
- abundance vs intensity? abundance
- Notame vs Notame workflow? Notame workflow
- repeated measures vs multiple time points? Multiple time points
- multimodal vs multi-modal? multimodal
- metabolomics vs metabolome? metabolome
